+#### PowerISA 2.01 (PowerPC 64-bit) support
+
+Node.js can be built for PowerISA 2.01 (PowerPC 64-bit) architectures
+using `-mcpu=powerpc64`, though this is experimental and not officially
+supported. To build:
+
+1. **Disable OpenSSL assembly optimizations** (required):
+   ```bash
+   ./configure --openssl-no-asm --dest-cpu=ppc64
+   ```
+
+2. **Set compiler flags** to target PowerISA 2.01:
+   ```bash
+   export CC="gcc -mcpu=powerpc64"
+   export CXX="g++ -mcpu=powerpc64"
+   ./configure --openssl-no-asm --dest-cpu=ppc64
+   make -j4
+   ```
+
+**Limitations:**
+- Reduced performance compared to Power8+ builds
+- Some V8 optimizations may be disabled
+- WebAssembly SIMD requires Power9+ and will not work
+- Not officially supported; may break in future updates
+- Requires thorough testing, especially for crypto operations
+
